+
+## Filing Decisions
+
+- Filed two new factual atoms under
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/` because the report adds
+  candidate-specific Step-2 Tao-screen verdicts that were not yet stored as
+  reusable library entries:
+  - divergence / stress form fails because integration by parts recreates the
+    same stress-against-`grad phi` burden
+  - Lamb-vector / Helmholtz-projected form fails because the same pressure,
+    projection, Calderon-Zygmund, and commutator debt returns after
+    localization
+- Did not create a third factual file for the report's common Step-2 screen,
+  because that criterion was already captured by the existing success rule and
+  localization-debt notes in the library.
+- Consolidated the meta note into
+  `library/meta/obstruction-screening/demand-estimate-level-action-on-the-live-obstruction.md`
+  instead of creating a near-duplicate meta file. The updated entry now asks
+  the rewrite-audit question in the sharper form:
+  after cutoff insertion, what exact coefficient becomes smaller, and what
+  ledger entry proves it?
+- Folded the note about auditing tempting algebraic cleanups side by side into
+  that same obstruction-screening entry to keep the meta library compact.
+
+## Duplicate Check
+
+- Searched the factual and meta libraries for overlap on `divergence / stress`,
+  `Lamb-vector`, `projected`, `Tao`, `smaller coefficient`, `ledger`, and
+  `localization debt`.
+- Found existing general coverage for:
+  - the fixed gain currency and same-protocol success criterion
+  - projected/Lamb rewrites owing localization debt
+  - the bounded Step-1 candidate family
+- Found no existing factual entry that already states the final Step-2
+  rejection reason for the divergence / stress candidate.
+- Found no existing factual entry that already states the final Step-2
+  rejection reason for the Lamb-vector / Helmholtz-projected candidate.
+- Found the report's operational note about an unfinished explorer scaffold to
+  be already covered by existing workflow-monitoring lessons on launcher stalls
+  and scaffold artifacts, so it was skipped as a duplicate.
+
+## Index Updates
+
+- Updated `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/INDEX.md` with the
+  two new candidate-verdict entries.
+- Updated `library/factual/INDEX.md` so the topic summary now mentions the
+  first Step-2 Tao-screen rejections for the fixed rewrite table.
+- Updated `library/meta/obstruction-screening/INDEX.md` and
+  `library/meta/INDEX.md` so the sharpened cutoff-and-ledger question is
+  discoverable from both topic levels.
+
+## Conflict Resolution
+
+- The report mixed already-filed branch-wide screening rules with genuinely new
+  candidate-specific verdicts. I resolved that by filing only the new verdicts
+  as factual atoms and treating the branch-wide screening language as duplicate
+  support for existing entries.
+- The meta note mixed a strengthened existing rule with a small comparative
+  audit tactic. I resolved that by merging both into one existing
+  obstruction-screening file rather than splitting them into two closely
+  related meta entries.
+
+## Deletion Policy
+
+- The inbox report and meta note were left in place as requested.

